WEBVTT

00:01.722 --> 00:03.718
- We're pulling the plug.
- And the kids know,

00:03.724 --> 00:04.959
and they're okay.

00:04.965 --> 00:07.316
And things really aren't
gonna be that different.

00:07.322 --> 00:10.095
The on-duty parent will live in here,

00:10.101 --> 00:12.278
taking care of the kids,
living a rich, full life.

00:12.284 --> 00:14.482
That's right. And the off-duty
parent will be living right

00:14.488 --> 00:16.113
here in the garage.

00:16.119 --> 00:17.886
I don't want Lena dating again.

00:17.892 --> 00:21.309
- I want her back together with Martin.
- We haven't had sex in two years.

00:22.292 --> 00:25.197
Let me give you my card, here.

00:25.203 --> 00:27.599
Are you... sending out vibes?

00:27.605 --> 00:30.009
- Vibes?
- Are we vibing?

00:30.622 --> 00:32.887
_

00:35.701 --> 00:38.324
Okay, so, Milo has a
book report due Monday,

00:38.330 --> 00:39.832
Mason needs to practice piano.

00:39.838 --> 00:41.411
At least an hour... that was the deal.

00:41.417 --> 00:44.211
- Okay.
- And Mae needs to take vitamin D.

00:44.217 --> 00:46.006
The doctor said she's deficient.

00:46.012 --> 00:47.787
There's some on the
counter by the microwave.

00:47.793 --> 00:49.036
She's deficient?

00:49.042 --> 00:51.352
How's that even possible? We
live in Southern California.

00:51.358 --> 00:52.662
Have you met Mae?

00:52.853 --> 00:54.053
What are you doing?

00:54.130 --> 00:56.332
Taking the comforter
with me to the garage.

00:56.338 --> 00:58.916
Um, no, you're not.

00:59.187 --> 01:01.404
I just spent a week in
solitary confinement.

01:01.410 --> 01:03.280
I've been looking forward to a real bed,

01:03.286 --> 01:06.393
complete with the
comfort of a comforter.

01:06.399 --> 01:08.208
Ooh! It's so cozy!

01:08.214 --> 01:10.114
You don't even care about blankets.

01:10.120 --> 01:12.412
- You kick them off at night.
- Yeah, but one has to be there

01:12.418 --> 01:13.711
in order for me to kick it off.

01:13.717 --> 01:15.528
And don't tell me that
I can kick off a quilt,

01:15.534 --> 01:17.623
because I've tried it,
sister. It didn't work!

01:17.629 --> 01:19.412
Uh, I'll get you a different blanket!

01:19.418 --> 01:21.086
- You're ridiculous.
- You're ridiculous!

01:21.092 --> 01:23.215
That comforter is property
of the master bedroom.

01:23.221 --> 01:24.742
Whoever sleeps here gets to enjoy

01:24.748 --> 01:28.118
full custody of that
blanket and the children.

01:28.124 --> 01:30.032
- Come here!
- Hey! Hey! Hey!

01:30.038 --> 01:33.007
- Stop it! Martin!
- Rahh! Ow!

01:33.100 --> 01:34.865
It wasn't always like this.

01:35.066 --> 01:36.453
When things were good,

01:36.459 --> 01:38.030
we slept under the same blanket.

01:38.036 --> 01:41.475
But once you introduce that
crappy second blanket, boy...

01:41.481 --> 01:43.860
Yeah, the marriage
is pretty much over.

01:44.657 --> 01:45.862
God!

01:45.868 --> 01:47.767
- Oh! Fine!
- Ow!

01:47.773 --> 01:50.264
- Uh!
- Let the baby have his blankie.

01:50.447 --> 01:51.751
Sank you!

01:53.424 --> 01:54.624
Hey.

01:54.797 --> 01:57.727
I'm sorry. I'll see you next week.

01:59.915 --> 02:03.014
- Thank you. I appreciate the...
- I was talking to the blanket.

02:05.372 --> 02:08.662
♪ Keep giving me hope for a better day ♪

02:08.668 --> 02:12.052
