- I surrender! I surrender!
- Gonna cry? Oh, you surrender?

02:29.423 --> 02:32.026
Oh, are you gonna
cry? Are you gonna cry?

02:32.032 --> 02:34.208
Do I need to get you
a crying bikini, huh?

02:34.214 --> 02:35.722
- Sexist.
- Ow! Ow!

02:36.708 --> 02:37.908
Beg pardon?

02:37.914 --> 02:40.295
You're a cisgendered sexist,
and you're raising two more

02:40.301 --> 02:43.280
by continuing to perpetuate
negative stereotypes.

02:43.780 --> 02:45.780
- Wha?
- "Crying bikini"?

02:45.786 --> 02:48.688
Because that's what girls
wear, and only girls cry?

02:48.694 --> 02:51.090
No, no, no. The crying bikini is a...

02:51.306 --> 02:53.518
it's a unisex garment, right?

02:54.895 --> 02:56.372
Oh, come on.

02:56.378 --> 02:58.890
Come on. I'm not sexist.
I'm your dad. I...

02:58.896 --> 03:01.258
always treated you
kids exactly the same.

03:01.264 --> 03:02.464
Really?

03:02.470 --> 03:04.378
Because you never wrestle with me.

03:04.384 --> 03:05.909
You want to wrestle?

03:07.217 --> 03:09.443
- Sure.
- Aww, she's gonna get it.

03:09.449 --> 03:12.521
- You asked for it. Rah! Uh!
- Oof!

03:12.527 --> 03:14.754
- Ooh!
- Oh, my God.

03:14.760 --> 03:16.936
- Oh, my God. Are you okay, honey?
- I'm okay.

03:16.942 --> 03:20.307
She just stood there like a drunk.

03:20.367 --> 03:22.684
- Is it over?
- Well, I mean, it can be.

03:22.690 --> 03:25.289
Technically, you're supposed
to, you know, struggle now,

03:25.295 --> 03:28.109
- try to get free.
- He's not even torturing her.

03:28.115 --> 03:30.309
Come on, Dad. What
about the rib cruncher?

03:30.315 --> 03:32.032
Yeah. That's your signature move.

03:32.038 --> 03:34.710
You want your ribs... crunched?

03:35.723 --> 03:36.932
Why not?

03:37.011 --> 03:40.620
Okay. Ah! The rib
cruncher... crunchin'...

03:40.626 --> 03:42.120
G-g-g-g-g... uh!

03:43.187 --> 03:45.409
She's impervious.

03:46.058 --> 03:47.356
Okay, that's it. We're done.

03:47.362 --> 03:49.133
Wrestling's over. Come on. Everyone. Go.

03:49.139 --> 03:50.636
- Aw.
- Go. Go read a book.

03:50.642 --> 03:53.057
No fair. Girls ruin everything.

03:53.063 --> 03:54.856
Hey, hey. Milo, get
over here. Come here.

03:55.358 --> 03:56.558
Come here.

03:57.687 --> 03:59.984
Don't say, "Girls ruin everything."

03:59.990 --> 04:03.476
It-it's not cool to
generalize about all girls.

04:04.072 --> 04:06.173
Say, "Mae ruins everything."

04:06.358 --> 04:08.190
I appreciate that.

04:10.139 --> 04:12.927
I'm sorry. Is it, like,
really damp in here?

04:12.933 --> 04:14.521
It is. Here.

04:14.618 --> 04:15.896
This should help.

04:18.515 --> 04:20.125
Huh. Look at those guys.

04:20.966 --> 04:22.902
- Are those...
- Centipedes, yeah.

04:23.060 --> 04:25.405
I've come to know
their habits quite well.

04:25.473 --> 04:27.677
They are a moisture-loving lot.

04:27.683 --> 04:31.009
But these boys flew a little
too close to the sun, am I right?

04:32.466 --> 04:34.480
- I'm sorry.
- What is it?

04:34.486 --> 04:36.364
I just hate seeing you like this?

04:36.370 --> 04:38.481
Like what? I'm happy.

04:38.487 --> 04:40.551
- You can't be.
- But I am.

04:40.557 --> 04:42.714
Camille, this is not that bad.

04:42.720 --> 04:44.353
And besides, it's only for a week.

04:44.359 --> 04:48.090
Actually, it's 26 weeks, if
the arrangement lasts a year.

04:48.096 --> 04:50.059
Well, I could see it
lasting more than a year.

04:50.065 --> 04:52.769
Honestly, I look forward
to my garage weeks.

04:52.775 --> 04:55.691
This is my time to focus on myself.

04:55.954 --> 04:59.076
I had an epiphany last
week in the main house.

04:59.974 --> 05:02.495
You know how our shower
has that great big skylight?

05:02.540 --> 05:04.440
- No.
- Well, it does.

05:04.446 --> 05:07.034
And I always insisted
that we never open it

05:07.040 --> 05:09.253
because of the squirrels
that run across our roof.

05:09.259 --> 05:10.459
It drove Martin crazy.

05:10.465 --> 05:12.229
He said, "What's the
point of having a skylight

05:12.235 --> 05:13.849
if we never get to open it?"

05:16.053 --> 05:17.853
I had a head full of shampoo...

05:17.859 --> 05:19.238
I'm gonna kill him.

05:19.346 --> 05:20.839
...and I was about to
get out of the shower

05:20.845 --> 05:22.642
to close the thing when...

05:26.139 --> 05:27.339
You wanna go?

05:28.390 --> 05:30.017
Don't even think about coming down here.

05:30.023 --> 05:31.414
I will kill a squirrel.

05:31.641 --> 05:34.008
And in that moment,
I realized something.

05:34.014 --> 05:36.814
That you were right and Martin
should have listened to you all along?

05:36.820 --> 05:39.220
No. That squirrel is the only man

05:39.226 --> 05:41.048
who has seen me naked in two years...

05:41.054 --> 05:42.486
and he's not even a man.

05:44.249 --> 05:46.032
This is my week to change that.

