- Bro, I'm taking it.
- Come at me, bro.

05:59.229 --> 06:01.724
- Don't say "come at me, bro" to your bro, bro.
- Here.

06:02.203 --> 06:04.537
Mae, you okay?

06:04.605 --> 06:08.801
Yeah, just... a little too much
bro-energy, if I'm being honest.

06:08.807 --> 06:11.541
Mmm, well, they are... actual bros.

06:11.547 --> 06:13.399
And I guess I didn't get
the memo about this being

06:13.405 --> 06:16.090
a shirtless dinner, or
I would have joined in.

06:16.096 --> 06:17.960
- Gross.
- My point exactly.

06:18.229 --> 06:20.348
Ditto for the recent no-flushing trend.

06:20.354 --> 06:23.042
- Hey, if it's yellow, let it mellow.
- Ah, that's a good boy.

06:23.048 --> 06:24.840
How is that a "good boy"?

06:24.846 --> 06:27.426
Mae, when you're a mom,
you can make the rules,

06:27.432 --> 06:29.239
but I'm playing Mom this week.

06:29.245 --> 06:31.354
And why are you "playing Mom"?

06:31.360 --> 06:34.463
Because you're taking care
of your kids and your house?

06:34.469 --> 06:36.448
He's not really taking
care of his house.

06:36.454 --> 06:38.463
I'm literally only shirtless
'cause there's no clean laundry.

06:38.469 --> 06:40.268
Shut up, traitors!

06:40.274 --> 06:42.434
Do you want clean laundry
or the Master Sword in Zelda?

06:42.440 --> 06:43.640
I can't do both.

06:44.112 --> 06:45.534
And besides...

06:45.747 --> 06:47.823
there was a whole movie
made about it in the '80s.

06:47.901 --> 06:49.237
It was called "Mr. Mom."

06:49.243 --> 06:51.647
You know what a better name
for that movie would have been?

06:51.831 --> 06:53.031
"Dad."

06:54.422 --> 06:55.919
- She's not wrong.
- Yep.

06:55.925 --> 06:58.403
- All right, guys. Zip it.
- He...

07:02.159 --> 07:04.454
_

07:05.179 --> 07:07.391
_

07:07.397 --> 07:08.671
Who are you texting?

07:08.984 --> 07:10.184
Mae.

07:10.190 --> 07:11.907
Why are you lying in wait?

07:11.913 --> 07:16.399
Sorry, but... Mom, I can't
handle Dad weeks. I just can't.

07:16.405 --> 07:19.784
Nobody brushes and nobody
flushes, and not to tattle,

07:19.790 --> 07:23.317
but Dad never moves the wet clothes
from the washer into the dryer.

07:23.700 --> 07:25.628
Can I please just
stay out here with you?

07:25.712 --> 07:27.227
Oh, sweetie.

07:27.414 --> 07:29.095
You know, I would love that,

07:29.101 --> 07:31.856
but I think your dad
would be heartbroken.

07:32.479 --> 07:36.039
I mean, he really looks
forward to his weeks with you.

07:36.125 --> 07:38.443
I mean, your dad adores you.

07:39.641 --> 07:42.444
You know who's a real pain
in the ass? Your daughter.

07:42.450 --> 07:44.133
I mean, when did she get so judgmental?

07:44.139 --> 07:46.446
Seriously, Mae can go topple
the patriarchy someplace else,

07:46.452 --> 07:48.046
because I am her actual father,

07:48.052 --> 07:50.216
and the next time that
girl rolls her eyes at me,

07:50.222 --> 07:51.422
I'm gonna tell her...

07:52.987 --> 07:54.804
The future is female?

07:58.685 --> 08:00.490
W-Well, what the hell is wrong with her?

08:00.496 --> 08:01.995
Maybe she feels outnumbered.

08:02.001 --> 08:04.205
Well, I'm sure Mason feels
the same way during your week.

08:04.211 --> 08:06.086
But he's not outnumbered. He has Milo...

08:06.092 --> 08:09.101
Oh, Milo doesn't count. He's,
like, a little half-human.

08:09.204 --> 08:11.103
Look. Mae is smart.

08:11.109 --> 08:12.356
And insightful.

08:12.362 --> 08:14.729
- And she's also...
- Not my daughter?

08:14.831 --> 08:16.732
- I was gonna say "a feminist."
- 'Cause you can tell me

08:16.738 --> 08:19.417
- if she's not my daughter.
- Mae is a budding feminist,

08:19.423 --> 08:22.636
- and as such, she is questioning everything.
- Okay.

08:22.642 --> 08:26.059
So, maybe if you just took a
little bit more of an interest

08:26.065 --> 08:27.536
in the things that she cares about,

08:27.542 --> 08:29.763
- the way you do with the boys.
- Oh god, here we go again.

08:30.155 --> 08:31.631
If you don't want my advice,

08:31.637 --> 08:33.727
I've got a whole shelf
full of parenting books...

08:34.121 --> 08:36.009
- and cookbooks.
- So, you're just gonna use this

08:36.015 --> 08:37.900
as an excuse to push your own agenda

08:37.907 --> 08:40.799
- once again. Oh, just admit it, Lena,
- You came knocking on my door.

08:40.804 --> 08:43.385
it kills you that I don't
parent the way you do.

08:43.390 --> 08:45.922
And yet, here I stand... not dead.

08:45.928 --> 08:48.353
And clearly, my rules
don't govern your world,

08:48.359 --> 08:49.738
- Right.
- hence the skylight.

08:49.766 --> 08:52.217
Oh, the skylight?

08:52.223 --> 08:53.524
The skylight!

08:53.530 --> 08:56.524
Oh, you're just angry because
you can't block my sunshine.

08:56.530 --> 08:59.048
I was eye-[BLEEP] by a squirrel!

08:59.733 --> 09:00.933
Whoa.

09:01.811 --> 09:04.222
- I didn't mean to block his sunshine,
- _

09:04.228 --> 09:05.927
but somehow, I'm always the bad guy.

09:05.933 --> 09:07.622
- Yeah.
- "Yeah"?

09:07.628 --> 09:09.418
Look, I realize that

09:09.424 --> 09:11.613
things between you
two are complicated...

09:11.619 --> 09:13.184
They're not complicated. They're over.

09:13.190 --> 09:16.200
...but then again, the devil you know...

09:16.206 --> 09:19.024
But then again, who wants
to be married to the devil?

09:19.030 --> 09:21.196
You should've heard the way
he talked to me last night.

09:21.202 --> 09:22.907
He blames me for everything,

09:22.913 --> 09:24.907
including his relationship with Mae.

09:24.913 --> 09:27.297
But on the plus side, not a squirrel.

09:27.303 --> 09:29.172
Fine, I'll give you "not a squirrel."

09:29.178 --> 09:31.171
But need I remind you, Martin's dating.

09:31.177 --> 09:34.696
We have no way of knowing
whether he is or isn't dating.

09:34.702 --> 09:37.282
Well, regardless, I am more interested

09:37.288 --> 09:39.079
in the cute doctor I've been texting.

09:39.085 --> 09:40.469
What cute doctor?

09:40.475 --> 09:43.355
The one who treated Mason. I
asked him out for drinks tonight.

09:43.526 --> 09:45.856
This is my mom's, but I'm allowed.

09:45.862 --> 09:47.565
- I know, Toby.
- So, what?

09:47.571 --> 09:50.548
You just use emojis
now, like some tween?

09:50.554 --> 09:52.009
- The heart-eyes one...
- _

09:52.015 --> 09:53.794
- The tongue-out one...
- _

09:53.800 --> 09:56.090
- The snorting-coke one...
- That's not coke.

09:56.096 --> 09:57.858
That is a ton of coke.

09:58.493 --> 10:00.122
Okay, relax, chip reader.

10:00.128 --> 10:02.101
We all waited for you, and
now, the second you're ready,

10:02.107 --> 10:03.421
Toby's supposed to jump?!

10:04.963 --> 10:07.055
I thought you'd be happy for me.

10:07.061 --> 10:08.869
- Well, I'm not.
- _

10:09.342 --> 10:12.547
I'm sorry. I just really miss
the way things used to be.

10:12.553 --> 10:13.938
Well, I don't,

10:13.944 --> 10:16.220
okay? I don't want a platonic marriage.

10:16.226 --> 10:18.430
I want to be with someone who's into me.

10:18.436 --> 10:21.637
I want to be with someone who
wants to tear my clothes off.

10:22.091 --> 10:25.990
Are you the type of person
who would let someone...

10:26.357 --> 10:27.705
tear their clothes off?

10:28.598 --> 10:32.874
Well, obviously not my high-end pieces.

10:34.655 --> 10:36.365
_

10:41.930 --> 10:43.330
"Gender Wars"?

10:43.517 --> 10:45.882
- Why are you looking at Mom's books?
- Oh.

10:46.631 --> 10:49.787
Hey, man. Uh, I'm just
doing a little research on

10:49.793 --> 10:51.045
your sister.

10:52.766 --> 10:54.099
And your mom.

10:54.105 --> 10:56.837
- And just women in general. You know.
- _

10:56.843 --> 10:59.147
- Care to join me?
- I'm good.

11:01.344 --> 11:03.971
I mean, it'd be one thing if she
were dating to get back at him,

11:03.977 --> 11:06.244
but I don't think
she's doing it for him.

11:06.250 --> 11:07.857
I think she's doing it for her.

11:07.863 --> 11:09.099
Which means...

11:09.105 --> 11:10.387
it's really over.

11:10.706 --> 11:12.098
That's a fair assumption.

11:14.810 --> 11:17.793
- I don't understand your attitude.
- What attitude?

11:17.799 --> 11:20.193
How can you take this
whole thing just lying down?

11:20.199 --> 11:22.099
Take what lying down?
Someone else's divorce?

11:22.105 --> 11:23.919
Well, if it could happen to them,

11:23.925 --> 11:25.904
- it could happen to us.
- It's not gonna happen to us.

11:25.910 --> 11:27.621
- Well, how do you know?
- 'Cause if you ever tried to leave,

11:27.627 --> 11:29.497
I would hold you captive like an orca.

11:29.503 --> 11:30.970
- That's illegal.
- What do I care?

11:30.976 --> 11:32.894
Without you, my life is over anyway.

11:33.696 --> 11:38.275
See, that is exactly the type of
needy, desperate, deranged behavior

11:38.281 --> 11:41.173
that it takes to keep
a marriage together.

11:43.528 --> 11:45.326
Sorry, I flushed.

11:49.212 --> 11:50.611
What's with the hats?

11:50.617 --> 11:52.043
Well, uh...

11:52.418 --> 11:55.135
we just wanted to show you
that we support your cause.

11:55.141 --> 11:56.443
My cause?

11:57.031 --> 11:58.739
You guys are hilarious.

12:04.026 --> 12:05.916
I told you this wasn't gonna work.

12:08.423 --> 12:10.147
I like mine.

12:11.272 --> 12:12.710
Whoa, are you cooking?

12:12.716 --> 12:15.782
Yeah. I just realized
that I did have a tendency

12:15.788 --> 12:17.651
to let Lena do most
of the household stuff,

12:17.657 --> 12:20.265
and now, I'm... trying to... you know...

12:20.271 --> 12:21.692
- Change?
- Yes.

12:21.698 --> 12:22.998
Change.

12:23.004 --> 12:24.555
W-Why now?

12:24.783 --> 12:27.653
Well, for starters,
my daughter hates me.

12:27.659 --> 12:29.653
I mean, I-I've already screwed
up my relationship with Lena.

12:29.659 --> 12:31.188
I don't want to lose Mae, too.

12:32.538 --> 12:34.838
Martin, you're so vulnerable right now.

12:36.143 --> 12:39.072
It's beautiful, bro.
It's seriously beautiful.

12:39.363 --> 12:42.269
- Can I give you a hug?
- I-I-I don't really want to do that.

12:42.275 --> 12:43.475
Come on.

12:43.654 --> 12:44.908
Let's hug.

12:46.865 --> 12:48.103
Okay.

12:53.428 --> 12:55.028
- Mmm.
- Ahh.

12:55.410 --> 12:56.635
It's all right.

12:59.557 --> 13:00.769
- Oh!
- Aah!

13:00.775 --> 13:02.591
Stay in the hug, all
right? Don't turn around.

13:02.597 --> 13:04.419
